cs.DC, cs.CE, cs.NA, cs.MS, cs.CY 

This paper discusses the use of science gateways for managing complex workflows and integrating distributed computing resources, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also focuses on the practical applications of these workflows in materials science, physics, chemistry, biology, and nanotechnologies, which could be categorized under Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE), Numerical Analysis (cs.NA), Modeling and Simulation (cs.MS), and Cybernetics (cs.CY).
